      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Slice your <strong>cucumber</strong> into discs</p><p>Add the <strong>cucumber discs</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cider</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong>, <strong>chopped dill</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and set aside to pickle – this is your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
