    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> – these are your <strong>parsley breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Pat your<strong> basa fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then add to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and sprinkle over the <strong>parsley breadcrumbs </strong>then put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through – this is your <strong>herb-crusted basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
